cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to summarize product titles in E-commerce applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to retain key information and deep learning models to handle the constraints of product title summarization, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. The paper also involves the use of soft gating mechanism and pointer network, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of real-world product titles, which may involve image processing techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category.
